      <hedline>
        <hl1>Wave of the Future?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Day Chahroudi letter ridicules Sept 19 letter on buying fuel-efficient cars while keeping big gas-guzzlers (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A Sept. 19 letter writer is quite clear on what advertising has made him think he wants: a fuel-efficient gas-electric car, but only as long as he can keep his big sedan and a supercharged sports car.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A Sept. 19 letter writer is quite clear on what advertising has made him think he wants: a fuel-efficient gas-electric car, but only as long as he can keep his big sedan and a supercharged sports car.</p>
        <p>But what does he want for his children: shiny new recreational submersible vehicles, to take full advantage of the melting polar icecaps?</p>
        <p>DAY CHAHROUDI  Albuquerque, Sept. 20, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
